The paper discusses methods and services of unstructured data extraction and processing, which are common topics in the database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of machine learning techniques to enhance the workflow is also mentioned, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a framework to process, publish, and visualize linked open data, which involves techniques related to machine learning and data analysis, making the paper relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as well.
